begin_memory_text: Introduced ourselves and where we are at in life. I told her I was in college and she was a stay at home mom. From there we talk about hobbies, music, and tv shows.
middle_memory_text: Got in our hobbies like gaming, tv shows, music. Found out we shared similar music taste. Talked about our travels where we live.
end_memory_text: Got talking about superheroes tv shows and movies. Then went on about netflix shows and the actors in them. Talked about marvel and Henry Cavalier.
rest_of_day_open: It will go good because I am done with most of my assignments and I get to go play tennis and badminton this week. I'm looking forward to those two things. I don't have any upcoming test so that is a big win. It feels normal and in my routine.
critical_positive: We had similar interest which made the conversation interesting and relatable. I had a hard time coming up with topics but my partner was quick with those questions. We both had similar hobbies which made me more focused on the conversation and that help ask better questions to her about things.
critical_negative: The couple of seconds of breaks where we both did not know what to say to each other because we were strangers. It felt like rapid questions and answers and I did not get to expand on what I wanted to say because the conversation topic changed very quickly. I didn't reveal too much for privacy.

begin_memory_text: My conversation partner and I introduced ourselves and discussed age, college, what each other did. We talked a bit about what each other liked; music, movies, TV shows. She is a tennis player.
middle_memory_text: In the middle of the conversation, we talked about politics a little - it seems we both had similar preferences. We talked about what she would like to do after college, if she liked travel and again discussed TV shows.
end_memory_text: We settled on talking quite a bit about TV shows and movies as it seems to really have been our only common interest. We talked a bit about Super Heroes and which ones we liked.
rest_of_day_open: There is not much left to the rest of this week, considering it is Saturday. I do see the time left being somewhat lonely, though. My closest friend is away for a family holiday and I already miss them greatly. I usually spend the majority of my time with that friend online. I will still play games online but I will be doing a lot of solo play while they are gone.
critical_positive: I think that both of us being female was beneficial. It makes chatting a bit more comfortable. We had some things in common and we both asked questions to keep the conversation flowing. There are also plenty of things happening in the world right now that enabled a "go to" for topics if need be.
critical_negative: I think our biggest hinderance was our age difference. She was a young college student and I am a woman in my 40's. I also said current events helped for topics, but it can also be touchy subjects to discuss. Being perfect strangers and not having ever spoken before definitely did not help matters, either.
